                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            The manuscript was written in <origPlace>Mondsee</origPlace> probably in the period <origDate notBefore="0811" notAfter="0819">811-819</origDate> by the order of Abbot <rs type="person">Lantpert</rs>. The manuscript can be dated based on the opening inscription mentioning <rs type="person">Hildebald of Cologne</rs> as archbishop. Hildebald became <foreign>Abbas Commendatarius</foreign> in 803, which can be seen as the <foreign>terminus post quem</foreign>, while Hildebald death in 819 as the <foreign>terminus ante quem</foreign>. Lantpert named himself <quote>abbas</quote> in the inscription suggesting the book was written after 811; before that Lantpertus was still a deacon. 
                            
                        </origin>
